<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-07-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="189" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Butler</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-19"><hi rend="italic">July 19,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In opinion of Department, citizenship assumed for purpose evading
                            extradition should not be allowed that effect. If Mexican Government
                            refuse surrender Rowe on this ground, urge this view. Inform Department
                            status case.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Adee</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>